com.sri.ai.util.collect

Class CartesianProductIterator<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sri.ai.util.collect.EZIterator<ArrayList<E>>
      • com.sri.ai.util.collect.CartesianProductIterator<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterator<ArrayList<E>>

    @Beta
public class CartesianProductIterator<E>
extends EZIterator<ArrayList<E>>
    A iterator over the Cartesian product of the ranges of a list of iterators. The constructor takes a list of iterator makers because each dimension but the first one will need to be iterated multiple times, so a new iterator will be needed for each sweeping. An iterator maker for a given key is required to make iterators over the same range every time.
    Author:
    braz
